{"word":"βόσκημα","slug":"βόσκημα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>βόσκημα</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:βόσκω'><el>βόσκω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>that which is fed</i> or <i>fatted</i>: in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>fatted beasts, cattle</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; of sheep, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; of horses, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; of pigs, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>food</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}